Dataset description: This file includes organized student-level data intended to investigate academic achievement and the variables that affect test scores. While the columns capture a variety of academic, behavioral, family, and school-related characteristics such study habits, attendance, motivation, resource access, parental participation, and learning environment, each row represents a single kid. The dataset is well-structured and appropriate for statistical analysis, machine learning tasks including regression and classification, and exploratory data analysis. Researchers and novices alike can simply use it to identify trends in student performance and create predictive models based on actual educational aspects.
Link: https://www.kaggle.com/datasets/ayeshasiddiqa123/student-perfirmance
